deck: Written by Grant Morrison, Batman Incorporated tells the tale of Batman as he expands the Bat Family across the globe.
description:
Volume 2

A "second wave" The New 52 title starring Batman, Damian Wayne and the rest of Batman Inc as they combat Talia al Ghul and her Leviathan forces, directly following the past volumes Batman, Incorporated and Batman Incorporated: Leviathan Strikes.

Although the title was one of the top-selling New 52 titles, the volume was concluded with Grant Morrison's final issue and issue #13, respectively, in July 2013. This also ended Grant Morrison's Batman epic that he began in 2006 with Batman & Son.

Written by: Grant Morrison (0, 1-10, 12-13); Chris Burnham (0, 11)

Illustrated by: Chris Burnham (1-13); Frazer Irving (0)

Collected Editions

  • Vol. 1: Demon Star (#0-6)
  • Vol. 2: Gotham's Most Wanted (#7-13)
  • Absolute Batman, Incorporated

For pre-Flashpoint, refer to Batman Incorporated vol. 1
name: Batman, Incorporated

description:
This is a magazine-sized, 64-page graphic novel adaptation of the Donald Goines novel, Daddy Cool.

Front Cover Blurb:

The story of a hit man's fearful vengeance in defense of his teenage daughter's honor

Back Cover Blurb:

Larry Jackson, better known to family and friends as Daddy Cool, is a black hit man. His clients know that he's the best. He can pull a trigger or toss a knife and never blink an eye. All that counts is the bread. That and his teenage daughter, Janet. Her love and respect mean everything to the big man, and he's given her presents and lots of his hit money in the hope of buying them. But Janet is taken in by the smooth-talking Ronald, a youngblood pimp out to make a name for himself on the streets. He sees Janet as a ripe piece of fluff who'll be the most valuable girl in his stable. Ronald calls Janet's father, Daddy Fool, but Daddy Cool is nobody's fool. He discovers what the pimp has done and goes into action with a fearful vengeance.
name: Daddy Cool
